1
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:08,520
(CREAKING)

2
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:15,560
What? (GRUMBLING)

3
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:30,360
(GRUNTING)

4
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:32,120
(CAR HONKING)

5
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:33,320
(GASPS)

6
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:40,120
-Oh, my stars! Are you all right?
-Yeah. I'm fine.

7
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:52,920
(BOTH LAUGHING)

8
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:02,400
-So I've got something for you.
-What?

9
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:10,280
-You kept it?
-Of course I kept it.

10
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:12,240
Why?

11
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:16,880
Because this exact leaf had to grow
in that exact way, in that exact place,

12
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:19,960
so that precise wind could tear it
from that precise branch

13
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:24,640
and make it fly into this exact face
at that exact moment.

14
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:30,920
And if just one of those
tiny little things had never happened,

15
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,640
I'd never have met you.

16
00:01:35,480 --> 00:01:38,920
Which makes this the most important leaf
in human history.

17
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,320
(THUNDER CRASHING)

18
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:00,440
-There!
-There.

19
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,960
-Go on, kick it.
-(WHISTLING)

20
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:05,240
Oh, my stars! Are you all right?

21
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:09,320
Fine. Marvellous! Refulgent!

22
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,680
Possibly a touch embarrassed.
That's not dangerous, is it?

23
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:13,920
-What's not?
-(WHISPERING) Embarrassment.

24
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,760
Not usually. Not to my knowledge.

25
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,840
Good! Hey? Phew!

26
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:20,240
(CHUCKLING) I am so sorry.
She wants to be Bryan Robson.

27
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:23,480
No worries, my fault. No harm done.

28
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,640
-Hello there...
-Clara.

29
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,040
Ah.

30
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,480
Hello there, Clara.

31
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:36,920
(CROW CAWING)

32
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,200
(SIGHING)

33
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,520
She's just a girl. How can she be?

34
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,320
She can't be!

35
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,720
She is! She can't be!

36
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:18,760
She's not possible!

37
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:21,360
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

38
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,040
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

39
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,080
(TARDIS DOOR OPENING)

40
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,840
(DOORBELL RINGING)

41
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:13,520
CLARA: So we're moving
through actual time?

42
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,560
So what's it made of, time?

43
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:18,960
I mean, if you can just
roll right through it,

44
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:21,200
it's got to be made of stuff,
like jam's made of strawberries,

45
00:04:21,280 --> 00:04:23,080
-so what's it made of?
-Well, not strawberries, no.

46
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:25,720
No, no, no. That would be unacceptable.

47
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:30,760
-And we can go anywhere?
-Within reason. Well, I say reason...

48
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,560
-So we could go backwards in time.
-And space, yes.

49
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,400
-And forwards in time.
-And space, totally.

50
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:38,600
So where do you want to go, hey?
What do you want to see?

51
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:43,600
I don't know.

52
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:45,040
Do you know when somebody asks you
what's your favourite book

53
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:47,160
and straightaway you forget
every single book that you've ever read?

54
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:49,800
-No, totally not.
-Well, that's a thing that happens.

55
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:53,160
-And? Back to the question.
-Okay, so...

56
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:56,080
So... So...

57
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:01,920
So I'd like to see...
I would like to see...

58
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,120
What I would like to see is...

59
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:09,240
something awesome.

60
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:22,800
-Can you feel the light on your eyelids?
-Mmm-hmm.

61
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:27,480
That is the light of an alien sun.

62
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:30,080
Forward a couple of steps.

63
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:32,200
Okay.

64
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:36,480
-Are you ready?
-Yes.

65
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,320
No! Yes.

66
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,960
Welcome to the Rings of Akhaten.

67
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,520
-It's...
-Ooh! Yeah, it is. It so completely is.

68
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:57,920
But wait. There is more.

69
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,520
-More what?
-Wait, wait, wait.

70
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,440
In about five...

71
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:02,920
four...

72
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:04,600
three...

73
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:07,760
Look at that.

74
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:16,480
-What is it?
-The pyramid of the Rings of Akhaten.

75
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:19,080
It's a holy site for
the Sound Singers of Akhate.

76
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:22,520
-The who of what?
-Seven worlds orbiting the same star,

77
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:27,440
all of them sharing the belief that
life in the universe originated here,

78
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,760
on that planet.

79
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:32,080
-All life?
-In the universe.

80
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,160
-Did it?
-Well...

81
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:39,360
it's what they believe.
It's a nice story.

82
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:44,440
Can we see it? Up close?

83
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:53,200
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

84
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,240
(ALIENS CHATTERING)

85
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:15,880
(ALL SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE)

86
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,720
-(GIGGLING)
-DOCTOR: I can't pay for that.

87
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,280
CLARA: Where are they from?

88
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,800
Oh, you know, the local system, mostly.

89
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:25,280
-And what do I call them?
-Well, let's see.

90
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:29,920
Ah, there go some Pan-Babylonians.
A Lugarlirakush.

91
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,600
Uh...some Eukanians.

92
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,960
A Hooloovoo.

93
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,200
Ah!

94
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:39,160
(CONVERSING IN ALIEN DIALECT)

95
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,680
That chap's a Terraberserker
of the Kodonian Belt.

96
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,160
You don't see many of them
around any more.

97
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:47,760
Ho-ho! That's an Ultramanta!

98
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:51,240
You know, I forget
how much I like it here.

99
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,640
We should come here more often.

100
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:54,520
-You've been here before?
-Yes, yes, yes.

101
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,880
I came here a long time ago
with my granddaughter.

102
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:00,200
Hang on!

103
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,480
(SNARLING)

104
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,560
Mmm!

105
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,040
Exotic fruit of some description.

106
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:16,080
All right, non-toxic,
non-hallucinogenic,

107
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:19,600
high in free radicals and low
in other stuff, I shouldn't wonder.

108
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,840
No?

109
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,760
So why is everyone here?

110
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:25,960
Ah! For the Festival of Offerings.

111
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,920
Takes place every 1,000 years or so
when the rings align.

112
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,680
It's quite a big thing locally,
like Pancake Tuesday.

113
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,680
-Oh!
-(GROWLS)

114
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,760
(BARKING)

115
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,480
Um, Doctor?

116
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:42,520
(BARKING)

117
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,880
What's happening? Why is it angry?

118
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,440
This isn't an it. It's a she.

119
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,960
Dor'een, meet Clara.
Clara, meet Dor'een.

120
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:50,560
-Dor'een?
-Loose translation.

121
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:52,960
She sounds a bit grumpy
but she's a total love, actually.

122
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,400
-Aren't you? Yes, you are.
-(PURRING)

123
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:57,360
You know, actually, she's just asking
you if you fancy renting a moped.

124
00:08:57,440 --> 00:09:00,160
(MIMICS MOPED HUMMING)

125
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,480
(DOR'EEN SNARLS)

126
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:02,720
(BARKS)

127
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,320
(BARKS)

128
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:08,920
-So how much does it cost?
-Not money. Something valuable.

129
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,840
Sentimental value. A photograph,
love letter, something like that.

130
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:14,320
That's what's used for currency here.

131
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:17,880
Psychometry. Objects psychically
imprinted with their history.

132
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,800
The more treasured they are,
the more value they hold.

133
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:21,880
-That's horrible.
-Much better than using bits of paper.

134
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,600
-Then you pay.
-With what?

135
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:25,960
You're a thousand years old,
you must have something you care about.

136
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,440
Hmm... (SCOFFING)

137
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,840
(CLARA LAUGHING)

138
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,720
Doctor?

139
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:37,960
Doctor?

140
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Oh!

141
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,680
Hi. You okay?

142
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:53,440
-Have you seen her?
-Who?

143
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,600
-The Queen of Years.
-Who?

144
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,680
(LIQUID DRIPPING)

145
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:22,080
Hello?

146
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,320
(ECHOING CRASH)

147
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:39,640
(FOOTSTEPS RUNNING)

148
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,240
(GASPING)

149
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,880
Hi.

150
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:45,360
Are you okay? Are you lost?

151
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:01,320
(PANTING)

152
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:05,600
(SHRIEKS)

153
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,240
(LAUGHS)

154
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,280
You all right?

155
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:23,360
-What are you doing?
-Hiding.

156
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,080
Oh. Why?

157
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:28,320
You don't know me?

158
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:31,360
Sorry, actually not.

159
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:34,760
-So why did you follow me?
-To help. You looked lost.

160
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:38,200
I don't believe you.

161
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:45,000
I've got no idea who you might be.
I've never been here before.

162
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:47,360
I've never been anywhere
like here before.

163
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:50,720
I just saw a little girl
who looked like she needed help.

164
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:52,360
-Really?
-Really really.

165
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,640
-Can you help me?
-That's why I'm still here.

166
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,720
Because I need to hide.

167
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:04,840
(DISTORTED, WHISPERY VOICE) Merry.

168
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:09,880
Where are you, Merry?

169
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:11,440
I know the perfect box.

170
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:16,920
Merry!

171
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,400
(SOFT GROWL)

172
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:23,320
Where are you, Merry?

173
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:29,880
-Merry!
-Merry!

174
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,440
(GROWLING)

175
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:50,320
(WHISTLING NONCHALANTLY)

176
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,000
What's this?

177
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:59,800
A spaceshippy-thing, timey, spacey.

178
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:02,280
-It's teeny.
-Ha! You wait.

179
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:05,200
(DOOR RATTLING)

180
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:07,600
-Oh, come on!
-What's wrong?

181
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:09,920
I don't know.

182
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,920
I don't think it likes me.

183
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:16,320
(KNOCKING)

184
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,280
Come on! Let me in!

185
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:20,240
Hey, hey, little girl!

186
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:22,160
My name's Merry.

187
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,080
(CLARA CLEARS THROAT)

188
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:36,000
So what's happening?

189
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:38,800
-Is someone trying to hurt you?
-No.

190
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,920
I'm just scared.

191
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,000
-Of what?
-Getting it wrong.

192
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:47,480
Okay, can you pretend like
I'm totally a space alien and explain?

193
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,720
I'm Merry Galel.

194
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,440
I'm really not local, sorry.

195
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:54,040
The Queen of Years?

196
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:57,640
They chose me when I was a baby,
the day the last Queen of Years died.

197
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,760
-Okay.
-I'm the vessel of our history.

198
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:05,520
I know every chronicle, every poem,
every legend, every song.

199
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:06,720
Every single one?

200
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,960
Blimey, I hated history.

201
00:14:10,080 --> 00:14:11,800
Now I have to sing a song
in front of everyone.

202
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:14,760
A special song,
I have to sing it to a god.

203
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,160
I'm really scared.

204
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:26,560
Everyone's scared when they're little.

205
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:30,360
I used to be terrified of getting lost.
I used to have nightmares about it.

206
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:32,320
And then, I got lost.

207
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:35,360
Blackpool Beach. Bank Holiday Monday,

208
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:37,800
about 10 billion people,
I was about six.

209
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,680
My worst nightmare come true.

210
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,040
What happened?

211
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:44,680
My world ended, my heart broke

212
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,440
and then my mum found me.

213
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,480
We had fish and chips
and she drove me home

214
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:54,040
and she tucked me up
and she told me a story.

215
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:56,520
Doesn't matter where you are,

216
00:14:56,600 --> 00:15:00,160
in the jungle or the desert
or on the moon.

217
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:06,080
However lost you might feel,
you'll never really be lost, not really.

218
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,400
Because I will always be here

219
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:12,840
and I will always come and find you.

220
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,000
Every single time.

221
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:21,440
(FADING) Every single time.

222
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:27,840
And you were never scared again?

223
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:33,000
Oh, I was scared lots of times,
but never of being lost.

224
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,320
So, this special song,
what are you scared of exactly?

225
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:42,400
Getting it wrong.
Making Grandfather angry.

226
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:45,040
And do you think you'll get it wrong?

227
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:48,240
Because I don't.
I don't think you'll get it wrong.

228
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:52,320
I think you, Merry Galel,
will get it very, very right.

229
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:07,320
(METALLIC CHATTERING)

230
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:26,480
-What have you been doing?
-Exploring.

231
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,120
Where are we going now?

232
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:39,240
CHORISTER: # Sleep, my precious king

233
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:46,240
# Lay down

234
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:54,240
# My warrior

235
00:16:56,680 --> 00:17:00,080
# Rest now

236
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:05,000
# My hero #

237
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:07,080
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

238
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,240
DOCTOR: (SHUSHING) Sorry, sorry.

239
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:29,440
-Excuse me, sorry, excuse me.
-CLARA: Sorry. Sorry.

240
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:31,600
(CLARA CLEARING THROAT)

241
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,840
-Are we even supposed to be here?
-Shh!

242
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:35,280
-But are we?
-Shh!

243
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,320
-Sorry.
-(GROWLING)

244
00:17:56,960 --> 00:18:01,920
# Akhaten

245
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:12,760
-# Lay down
-MERRY: # Akhaten

246
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:16,440
# My king

247
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:24,560
# Sleep now eternal

248
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:31,000
# Sleep, my precious king

249
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:36,360
# Lay down

250
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:40,040
# O God of Akhaten

251
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:41,760
Oh, look.

252
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:44,440
They're singing to the mummy
in the temple.

253
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:48,120
They call it the Old God,
sometimes Grandfather.

254
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:55,280
# O God of Akhaten

255
00:18:56,120 --> 00:18:57,160
What are they singing?

256
00:18:58,560 --> 00:19:00,000
The Long Song.

257
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:06,160
A lullaby without end,
to feed the Old God. Keep him asleep.

258
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:11,400
It's been going for millions of years,
Chorister handing over to Chorister

259
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:14,320
generation after generation
after generation.

260
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:17,960
# Akhaten #

261
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:20,680
(ALIEN SNORTING)

262
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,560
-What are they doing?
-These are offerings.

263
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,920
Gifts of value.

264
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:29,720
Mementos to feed the Old God.

265
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:31,240
(CHUCKLING)

266
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:34,520
# O God of

267
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:37,840
# O God of
O God of

268
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:43,960
# Sleep, my precious king
# Akhaten

269
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,160
(LAUGHS)

270
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:49,600
(ALL SINGING)

271
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:58,920
# Lay...

272
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:02,400
ALL: # Lay down

273
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:06,360
# Akhaten

274
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:11,800
# O God of
O God of

275
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:14,160
# O God of

276
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:21,080
# 0 God of Akhaten
# Rest now your heart...

277
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:23,480
(RUMBLING)

278
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:28,760
(GASPING)

279
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:36,560
# Old God

280
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:41,320
# Protect us

281
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:46,320
# Old God, protect... #

282
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:50,000
Okay, what's happening?
Is that supposed to happen?

283
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:53,400
-(SCREAMING)
-Is somebody going to do something?

284
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,880
Excuse me,
is somebody going to help her?

285
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:56,560
(MERRY SCREAMING)

286
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:01,000
Why are we walking away?

287
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:03,480
We can't just walk away.

288
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,960
This is my fault,
I talked her into doing this.

289
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:09,320
Listen, there is one thing you need
to know about travelling with me.

290
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:11,680
Well, one thing apart from the blue box
and the two hearts.

291
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,760
We don't walk away.

292
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:17,320
(SOBBING)

293
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,480
(BARKING)

294
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:24,920
(GROWLING)

295
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:29,800
-I need something precious.
-Well, you must have something.

296
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:31,600
All the places you've seen,
there must be something.

297
00:21:31,680 --> 00:21:34,080
This. And I don't want to give it away
because it comes in handy.

298
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:35,840
You're a thousand years old
and that's it? Your spanner?

299
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,000
Screwdriver.

300
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:44,920
It was my mum's.

301
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,920
(GROWLING SOFTLY)

302
00:22:22,160 --> 00:22:23,240
CLARA: Merry!

303
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:29,600
(SCREAMING)

304
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:31,880
Wait! Wait!

305
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:34,960
(BOTH SCREAMING)

306
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:41,760
-Okay. Time to let go.
-I can't.

307
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:42,880
-Clara, you have to.
-Why?

308
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,160
-Because it really hurts.
-Sorry.

309
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,680
(WHIRRING)

310
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:50,560
Oh, that is interesting,
a frequency-modulated acoustic lock.

311
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:52,960
The key changes 10 million zillion
squillion times a second.

312
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:55,760
-Can you open it?
-Technically, no. In reality, also no.

313
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:58,320
-But still, let's give it a stab.
-Oh!

314
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:05,640
CHORISTER: # Don't wake from slumber
Old God, never wake from slumber #

315
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:08,320
CLARA: How can they just
stand there and watch?

316
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,000
Because this is sacred ground.

317
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:12,160
-But she's a child!
-Yeah, and he's a god.

318
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:14,000
Well, he is to them, anyway.

319
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:21,040
# Do not wake from slumber, Old God
Do not wake from slumber

320
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:26,320
# Rest your weary holy head
and cast our lives asunder

321
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:28,680
# Do not wake from slumber... #

322
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:31,200
I don't know what to do next.

323
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:33,280
What happens?

324
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,680
(SCREAMING)

325
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:39,600
CLARA: Merry! Merry, hold on!
We'll be there soon!

326
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:41,240
-Doctor.
-Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.

327
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:42,560
-Oh, hello.
-Hello what?

328
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:44,160
Sonic locked onto
the acoustic tumblers.

329
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:46,800
-Meaning?
-Meaning I get to do this.

330
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:58,760
Ah! Hello there, I'm the Doctor.

331
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:01,520
And you met Clara, she was supposed
to be having a nice day out.

332
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,760
Still, it's early yet.

333
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:05,880
Are you coming, then?

334
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:08,440
Did I mention
that the door is immensely heavy?

335
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:10,240
Leave! You'll wake him.

336
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:12,160
Really quite extraordinarily heavy.

337
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,480
(GRUNTING)

338
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:16,000
-Clara!
-Uh-huh.

339
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:20,080
# ...from slumber, Old God,
never wake from slumber... #

340
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:23,440
-Merry, we need to leave.
-No! Go away.

341
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:24,760
CLARA: Not without you.

342
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:27,280
You said I wouldn't get it wrong
and then I got it wrong.

343
00:24:27,360 --> 00:24:29,120
And now this has happened.
Look what's happened!

344
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,320
You didn't get it wrong.

345
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:32,840
How do you know?
You don't know anything!

346
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:35,240
You have to go.
Go now or he'll eat us all.

347
00:24:35,320 --> 00:24:38,400
Well, he's ugly but you know,
to be honest...

348
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:43,640
I don't think he looks big enough.

349
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:46,120
Not our meat, our souls.

350
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:01,880
He doesn't want you, he wants me.

351
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,880
If you don't leave,
he'll eat you all up, too.

352
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:05,720
Yes. And you don't want that, do you?

353
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:10,600
You want us to walk out of this
really quite astonishingly heavy door

354
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:12,480
and never come back.

355
00:25:12,560 --> 00:25:15,760
-Yes.
-I see. Right. Clarified.

356
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:18,040
Absolutely never going to happen.

357
00:25:19,680 --> 00:25:21,040
(VOCALISING)

358
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:30,320
-Did you just lock us in?
-Yep.

359
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:32,840
-With the soul-eating monster?
-Yep.

360
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,320
And is there actually a way to get out?

361
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:36,120
What? Before he eats our souls?

362
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,920
-Ideally, yeah.
-Possibly.

363
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:41,200
-Probably. There usually seems to be.
-(CHORISTER CONTINUES SINGING)

364
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:43,960
Doctor, why's he still singing?

365
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:46,640
# ...God, rest your weary holy head... #

366
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:48,640
He's trying to sing
the Old God back to sleep,

367
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:50,840
but that's not going to happen.
He's waking up, mate.

368
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:54,600
He's coming, ready or not.
You want to run.

369
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:56,600
# .. .head and... #

370
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:02,120
That's it, then? Song's over?

371
00:26:02,840 --> 00:26:04,480
The song is over.

372
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:11,040
My name is Chorister Asbethix

373
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:12,880
and the Long Song

374
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,840
ended with me.

375
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:21,520
That's it, then, song's over.

376
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:24,240
(SNARLING)

377
00:26:24,320 --> 00:26:27,240
-Well! Ah, look at that!
-You've woken him!

378
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:29,640
-It's awake? What's it doing?
-(SNARLING)

379
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:32,520
Oh, you know, having a nice rest.

380
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:34,520
No, we didn't wake him
and you didn't wake him, either.

381
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:37,640
He is waking because it's his time
to wake and feed.

382
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:39,720
On you, apparently, on your story.

383
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:42,680
-She didn't say story, she said soul.
-Same thing.

384
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:44,800
The soul's made of stories, not atoms.

385
00:26:44,880 --> 00:26:48,560
Everything that ever happened to us,
people we love, people we lost,

386
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,480
people we found again
against all the odds.

387
00:26:50,560 --> 00:26:53,120
He threatens to wake,
they offer him a pure soul,

388
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:54,960
the soul of the Queen of Years.

389
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:56,520
-(SOFTLY) Stop it. You're scaring her.
-Good.

390
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:58,560
She should be scared,
she's sacrificing herself,

391
00:26:58,640 --> 00:27:01,640
she should know what that means.
Do you know what it means, Merry?

392
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:05,400
-A god chose me.
-It's not a god.

393
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:07,640
It'll feed on your soul
but that doesn't make it a god.

394
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:11,480
It is a vampire and you don't
need to give yourself to him.

395
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:15,520
Hey, do you mind if I tell you a story?
One you might not have heard.

396
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:20,600
All the elements in your body were
forged many, many millions of years ago,

397
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:25,400
in the heart of a faraway star
that exploded and died.

398
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:32,280
That explosion scattered those elements
across the desolations of deep space.

399
00:27:32,360 --> 00:27:35,800
After so, so many millions of years,

400
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:40,200
these elements came together
to form new stars and new planets

401
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:42,280
and on and on it went.

402
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:45,240
The elements came together
and burst apart,

403
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:50,040
forming shoes and ships
and sealing wax and cabbages and kings.

404
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:55,880
Until, eventually,
they came together to make you.

405
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:00,800
You are unique in the universe.

406
00:28:01,760 --> 00:28:05,000
There is only one Merry Galel.

407
00:28:06,840 --> 00:28:09,240
And there will never be another.

408
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:15,960
Getting rid of that existence
isn't a sacrifice, it is a waste.

409
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:22,600
So if I don't, then everyone else...

410
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,720
-Will be fine.
-(OLD GOD GROWLING)

411
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:28,400
-But how?
-There's always a way.

412
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:30,400
You promise?

413
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:35,200
Cross my hearts.

414
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:51,360
CLARA: Having a nice stretch?

415
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:53,480
(LOUD RUMBLING)

416
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:55,560
Something's coming. What's coming?

417
00:28:56,480 --> 00:28:57,640
The Vigil.

418
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:59,480
And what's the Vigil?

419
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:01,800
If the Queen of Years is unwilling
to be feasted upon...

420
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:02,960
DOCTOR: Yes?

421
00:29:03,040 --> 00:29:05,040
It's their job
to feed her to Grandfather.

422
00:29:11,080 --> 00:29:12,440
VIGIL: Merry.

423
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:14,920
MERRY: I'm sorry. I'm sorry!

424
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:18,360
-Don't you dare.
-Yep. Stay back! I'm armed!

425
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:21,200
-With a screwdriver.
-(ROARING)

426
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:25,280
Whoa!

427
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:26,880
(ROARING)

428
00:29:32,360 --> 00:29:33,760
(SNARLING)

429
00:29:42,360 --> 00:29:44,520
VIGIL: Here...

430
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:45,880
(GROWLING)

431
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:53,560
Clara, the sonic.

432
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:00,960
(ROARING)

433
00:30:05,840 --> 00:30:07,600
(DOCTOR SHOUTING)

434
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:10,880
You know all the stories. You must know
if there's another way out.

435
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:13,200
(STAMMERING) There's a tale.

436
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:16,600
A secret song, the people
of the temple only knew this door.

437
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:18,600
And the secret songs
open the secret door?

438
00:30:18,680 --> 00:30:20,760
How does it go? Can you sing it?

439
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:24,840
(VOCALISING)

440
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:34,320
DOCTOR: Go!

441
00:30:51,520 --> 00:30:53,400
(OLD GOD SNARLING)

442
00:30:58,760 --> 00:30:59,880
Doctor!

443
00:31:08,320 --> 00:31:09,560
(WHIRRING)

444
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:21,520
(ROARING)

445
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:32,320
(GROWLING SOFTLY)

446
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:33,520
CLARA: Where did they go?

447
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:37,960
Grandfather's awake.
They're of no function any more.

448
00:31:38,680 --> 00:31:40,320
Well, you could sound happier about it.

449
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:41,840
(RUMBLING)

450
00:31:46,840 --> 00:31:49,080
Actually, I think I may have made
a bit of a tactical boo-boo.

451
00:31:49,160 --> 00:31:50,840
More of a semantics mix-up, really.

452
00:31:50,920 --> 00:31:51,960
What boo-boo?

453
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:54,000
I thought the Old God
was Grandfather but it wasn't,

454
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:55,760
it was just Grandfather's alarm clock.

455
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:58,480
Sorry, a bit lost.
Who's the Old God? Is there an Old God?

456
00:31:58,560 --> 00:32:00,360
Unfortunately, yes.

457
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:03,640
(RUMBLING)

458
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,280
Oh, my stars.

459
00:32:13,120 --> 00:32:14,400
What do we do?

460
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:18,120
Against that? I don't know. Do you know?
I don't know. Any ideas?

461
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:21,440
But you promised. You promised.

462
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:23,560
I did. I... I did promise.

463
00:32:23,680 --> 00:32:24,720
He'll eat us all.

464
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:28,200
He'll spread across the system,
consuming the seven worlds.

465
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:29,640
And when there's no more to eat,

466
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:32,320
he'll embark on a new odyssey
among the stars.

467
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:39,680
- I say leg it.
-Leg it where, exactly?

468
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:42,440
-Don't know. Lake District?
-Oh, the Lake District's lovely.

469
00:32:42,520 --> 00:32:44,520
Let's definitely go there.
We can eat scones.

470
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:47,360
They do great scones in 1927.

471
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:49,120
(RUMBLING)

472
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:50,640
You're going to fight it, aren't you?

473
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:53,520
Regrettably, yes.
I think I may be about to do that.

474
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:55,120
-It's really big.
-I've seen bigger.

475
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:57,600
-Really?
-Are you joking? It's massive!

476
00:32:58,200 --> 00:32:59,240
-I'm staying with you.
-No, you're not.

477
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:01,960
-Yes, I am. I can assist.
-No, you can't.

478
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:04,400
What about that stuff you said?

479
00:33:05,080 --> 00:33:07,440
We don't walk away.

480
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:14,600
No. We don't walk away.

481
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:18,160
But when we're holding on to
something precious, we run.

482
00:33:18,240 --> 00:33:21,000
We run and run, fast as we can.

483
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:25,360
And we don't stop running
until we are out from under the shadow.

484
00:33:27,760 --> 00:33:29,640
Now, off you pop.

485
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:32,160
Take the moped, I'll walk.

486
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:45,040
Any ideas?

487
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:48,280
No, didn't think so.

488
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:51,880
Righty-ho, then.

489
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:08,080
(RUMBLING)

490
00:34:08,160 --> 00:34:09,320
Lordy.

491
00:34:10,240 --> 00:34:12,040
Isn't he frightened?

492
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:16,120
I think he is.
I think he's very frightened.

493
00:34:16,280 --> 00:34:18,080
-I want to help.
-So do 1.

494
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:32,160
# Rest now

495
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:39,720
# My warrior

496
00:34:42,520 --> 00:34:44,760
# Rest now #

497
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:47,800
-Okay, then. That's what I'll do.
-(MERRY CONTINUES SINGING)

498
00:34:49,960 --> 00:34:52,720
I will tell you a story.

499
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:58,280
# ...world then

500
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:05,440
ALL: # Live

501
00:35:05,720 --> 00:35:08,320
# Wake up

502
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:13,280
# Wake up

503
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:17,480
# And let the cloak

504
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:20,360
# Of life

505
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:23,680
# Cling to your bones #

506
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:26,040
Can you hear them?

507
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:31,240
All these people who lived in terror
of you and your judgement,

508
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:34,800
all these people
whose ancestors devoted themselves,

509
00:35:34,920 --> 00:35:36,960
sacrificed themselves to you.

510
00:35:39,280 --> 00:35:40,680
Can you hear them singing?

511
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:44,440
# Live

512
00:35:45,760 --> 00:35:48,360
# Wake up #

513
00:35:48,600 --> 00:35:51,560
DOCTOR: Oh, you like to think
you're a god.

514
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:53,360
But you're not a god.

515
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:55,440
You're just a parasite,

516
00:35:55,520 --> 00:36:00,600
eaten out with jealousy and envy
and longing for the lives of others.

517
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:03,120
You feed on them.

518
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:09,000
On the memory of love and loss and birth
and death and joy and sorrow, so...

519
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:14,480
So...come on, then.

520
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:16,960
Take mine.

521
00:36:18,920 --> 00:36:21,120
Take my memories.

522
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:24,480
But I hope you've got a big appetite.

523
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:29,040
Because I've... (GRUNTING)
...lived...a long life.

524
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:31,840
And I have seen a few things.

525
00:36:32,160 --> 00:36:34,680
MERRY: # Wake up

526
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:38,680
# And let the cloak

527
00:36:39,680 --> 00:36:42,000
# Of life

528
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:43,760
# Cling to your bones #

529
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:47,120
DOCTOR: I walked away
from the last great time war.

530
00:36:47,200 --> 00:36:50,360
I marked the passing of the Time Lords.

531
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:54,600
I saw the birth of the universe
and I watched as time ran out,

532
00:36:55,320 --> 00:36:58,320
moment by moment,
until nothing remained.

533
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:00,680
No time, no space.

534
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:02,680
Just me!

535
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:06,600
I walked in universes
where the laws of physics were devised

536
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:09,480
by the mind of a madman.

537
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:15,880
And I watched universes freeze
and creations burn.

538
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:18,880
I have seen things you wouldn't believe!

539
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:23,160
I have lost things
you will never understand!

540
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:24,520
And I know things.

541
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:29,040
Secrets that must never be told,
knowledge that must never be spoken.

542
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:33,760
Knowledge that will make
parasite gods blaze!

543
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:37,040
So, come on, then!

544
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:40,800
Take it! Take it all, baby!

545
00:37:41,160 --> 00:37:44,360
Have it! You have it all!

546
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:51,960
MERRY: # Wake up

547
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:58,560
# Wake up #

548
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:04,520
(RUMBLING)

549
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:18,200
And I will always come and find you.

550
00:38:20,680 --> 00:38:22,680
Every single time.

551
00:38:25,680 --> 00:38:27,240
We don't walk away.

552
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:31,640
(GROANING)

553
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:49,200
(RUMBLING CONTINUES)

554
00:38:55,520 --> 00:38:57,000
Still hungry?

555
00:39:00,160 --> 00:39:03,480
Well, I've brought something for you.

556
00:39:05,280 --> 00:39:06,880
This.

557
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:09,720
The most important leaf
in human history.

558
00:39:11,080 --> 00:39:12,120
(GRUNTS)

559
00:39:14,160 --> 00:39:16,920
The most important leaf
in human history.

560
00:39:21,360 --> 00:39:24,440
It's full of stories. Full of history.

561
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:27,800
(LAUGHING)

562
00:39:28,200 --> 00:39:30,080
And full of a future
that never got lived.

563
00:39:32,440 --> 00:39:35,200
Days that should have been
that never were,

564
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,960
passed on to me.

565
00:39:44,600 --> 00:39:47,920
This leaf isn't just the past.
It's a whole future that never happened.

566
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:49,760
There are billions and millions
of unlived days

567
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:52,400
for every day we live, an infinity.

568
00:39:52,480 --> 00:39:54,240
All the days that never came.

569
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:56,920
And these are all my mum"s.

570
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:59,080
Well, come on, then.

571
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:01,680
Eat up.

572
00:40:03,520 --> 00:40:04,960
Are you full?

573
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,160
I expect so.

574
00:40:08,160 --> 00:40:10,960
Because there's quite a difference,
isn't there,

575
00:40:11,040 --> 00:40:14,360
between what was
and what should have been.

576
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:20,720
There's an awful lot of one
but there's an infinity of the other.

577
00:40:28,040 --> 00:40:30,320
And infinity is too much,

578
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:33,600
even for your appetite.

579
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:35,480
(RUMBLING)

580
00:40:51,400 --> 00:40:53,200
(WHOOSHING)

581
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:02,240
Home again, home again, jiggety-jig.

582
00:41:07,640 --> 00:41:09,240
It looks different.

583
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:12,320
No. Same house, same city, same planet.

584
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:15,840
Ha-hey! Same day, actually, huh?
Ooh, not bad.

585
00:41:17,520 --> 00:41:18,920
Hole in one!

586
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:20,080
You were there.

587
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:23,280
At Mum's grave, you were watching.

588
00:41:26,240 --> 00:41:30,440
-What were you doing there?
-I don't know. I was just making sure.

589
00:41:30,520 --> 00:41:31,640
Of what?

590
00:41:38,360 --> 00:41:41,240
-You remind me of someone.
-Who?

591
00:41:41,920 --> 00:41:44,200
Someone who died.

592
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:50,440
Well, whoever she was,
I'm not her, okay?

593
00:41:51,680 --> 00:41:54,240
If you want me to travel with you,
that's fine.

594
00:41:54,320 --> 00:41:55,400
But as me.

595
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:57,120
I'm not a bargain-basement stand-in
for somebody else.

596
00:41:57,200 --> 00:42:00,640
-I'm not going to compete with a ghost.
-No.

597
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:10,760
They wanted you to have it.

598
00:42:11,360 --> 00:42:13,080
-Who did?
-Everyone.

599
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:15,320
All the people you saved.

600
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:24,880
You. No one else.

601
00:42:25,120 --> 00:42:26,160
Clara.

602
00:42:48,360 --> 00:42:49,960
Alarm!

603
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:51,800
DOCTOR: How many were there left?

604
00:42:52,880 --> 00:42:53,960
Twelve.

605
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:55,920
This sub's stuffed
with nuclear missiles.

606
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,840
What are you going to do
when he finds that out?

607
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,040
Bring her up!

608
00:42:59,120 --> 00:43:00,160
Who's there?

609
00:43:00,240 --> 00:43:02,040
MAN: We are all that stands
between this creature

610
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:03,600
and the destruction of the world.

611
00:43:05,440 --> 00:43:06,560
He's arming the warheads.

612
00:43:07,640 --> 00:43:09,400
DOCTOR: Clara, get out of there.
Get out!

613
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:14,480
I will blow this sub up before
you can even reach that button.

